        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> in my opinion, you should just forget about int stuff and go with HP items.  i currently have 170 int, and i never even come close to running OOM.  Realistically, in most cases, mana regen is going to be much more important than your total mana pool.  Unless you regularly unload from FM to OOM, you should go with HPs.  With higher HPs overall, you can lich lower, which means that you wont have to BoD it back as soon.  </P><P>ok, so here are some things i would buy</P><P>6/65 rings 500pp each<BR>65/65 neck 800pp i think, thats what i paid for mine<BR>spider fur belt 300-500pp <BR>there is a 8 str 6 sta 35 hp back slot item that drops in kael, and even tho i wear one, i can never remember what its called, i think it sells for 800 pp or so, not sure, but you could pick up one of those</P><P>also in kael, sickly glowing orb.  range slot item, 60 hps and 5 sta, or maybe its 80 hps, cant remember, but you should be able to pick this up cheap, cause most people think its junk, at least the 20 people i was with in kael did when it dropped and they gave it to me without anyone even rolling.</P><P>netted kelp shoes, these have some str, int and 14 sta, i think they sell for 500pp, cant remember tho</P><P><BR> </font></td>
