        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Not long ago everyone got on a kick that HP &gt; INT, I personally don't agree.  </P><P>Your regen rate is ultimately very important, but just because you have a ton of HPs doesn't mean you can cast more.  You're still losing HPs at the same rate and still have to cast a lifetap just as many times to get those HPs back.  You certainly don't want to neglect HPs, but I do not agree that it's more important then INT/Mana.</P><P><BR>Insert witty comment and original artwork here.</P><P>Corto Muerte<BR>44 Gnecromancer</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Xavis</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The primary reason for going HP over int/mana is our line of hp to mana conversion spells.  Since you will be almost always using them, you will rarely be at full health, so every HP item is that many more ticks you can safely keep lich up.  But get int to 200 since it effects fizzle rates and at 50th level you will get 10 mana/int up to that point, but only 5 mana/int 201+.</P><P>Equipment ideas - unfortunately mostly they require Velious/Luclin:  Coldain skin boots/gloves run about 2K each.  Try to join a Kael arena raid for cloth quest drops, a wristband of strategy, sickly glowing orb, and giant scalemail pants AC 11 int 3 wis -3 hp 20 weight (ugh) 11.  Get a partner or a small group and go to the Tower of Frozen Shadow.  Camp floor 2 for the student's homework (ranged), floor 3 for a sorcerous bowl (primary), and floor 5 for a diamond wedding band.  The Coldain shawl quests can be soloed through #4.  Read up on Allakazam's about them - and on #4 be sure to read how Jobaber can help you track down the dwarf spawn.  You could hit Sol A for a molten cloak, or perhaps a Grey group for a shisshar scaled one.  You could probably get a nightshade wreath (5 int) a lot cheaper than the runed cowl.</P><P>Xavis<BR>Heretic of the Brood</P><P>Death is but a doorway.<BR>Here, let me help you with that...</font></td>
